		<s1 title="Goal">
			<p>This document lists all available serializers of Apache Cocoon and
                     describes their purpose.</p>
		 </s1>
		 <s1 title="Overview">
			<p>A serializer is the end point of an xml pipeline. It transform SAX 
                     events in binary or char streams for final client consumption. For more information about transformers
                     see <link href="../concepts/sitemap.html">the sitemap</link>.
      	      </p>
		 </s1>
		 <s1 title="The Serializers in Apache Cocoon">
